title: Clean Energy Poll Graphic 2 - 100 percent renewable
keywords: GSG poll, climate change, Massachusetts voters, clean energy
alt_text: Colored bar graph showing 44% strongly support and 21% support Massachusetts' goal of receiving 100% of electricity from renewable sources.

title: Clean Energy Poll Graphic 3 - 100 percent renewable
keywords: GSG poll, climate change, Massachusetts voters, clean energy
alt_text: Colored bar chart showing percentages of Massachusetts voters wanting more vs. less of different electricity fuel types. 88% want more solar and 85% want more wind. Numbers decline for Natural Gas (44%), Nuclear (26%), Oil (18%), and Coal (14%)

title: Clean Energy Poll Graphic 4 - policy opinions
keywords: GSG poll, climate change, Massachusetts voters, clean energy
alt_text: Bar graphs showing majorities of Massachusetts voters support providing incentives for people to make their homes and businesses more efficient (92%), and incentives for people to switch from propane, oil, and gas to cleaner alternatives (82%).

title: Clean Energy Poll Graphic 6 - Trusted Messengers
keywords: GSG poll, climate change, Massachusetts voters, clean energy
alt_text: Bar graph showing how much Massachusetts voters trust different messengers on the topic of energy. Scientists and public health experts are the most trusted. The president, utilities, and business leaders are the least trusted.
